RFC2535 is the RFC number that defines DNSSEC. DNSSEC provides mechanisms for verifying the authenticity of DNS data and the integrity of DNS messages. The purpose of DNSSEC is to ensure that the data being distributed over the DNS network is accurate and not maliciously altered.},
