{"question_id": 1657, "answer": B) ssh-keygen},
{"question_id": 1658, "answer": 回答：C

解释：
选项A和B的设置是错误的，因为它们分别允许或禁止root账户的SSH登录权限，而不是限制它。

选项C的正确设置是将`PermitRootLogin`设置为`no`，这将会阻止root用户通过SSH登录。

选项D的设置也是错误的，因为`PermitRootLogin prohibit-password`在某些SSH版本中可能表示禁止root通过密码登录，但在其他版本中可能是禁止root通过SSH密钥登录。因此，这部分设置可能不是所有情况下的正确选项。

综上所述，正确的选项是C，即在`/etc/ssh/sshd_config`文件中添加或修改`PermitRootLogin no`指令，以限制root账户的SSH登录权限。},
{"question_id": 1659, "answer": The correct answer is A. The command to set the default policy to deny all incoming connections would be:
```
sudo ufw default deny incoming
```
This command sets the default policy for incoming traffic to be denied, meaning that any incoming connections that do not have a corresponding rule in UFW will be rejected. The other options B, C, and D are not correct because they set the default policy for outgoing traffic or allow established connections, which are not the intended behavior.},
