{"question_id": 3320, "answer": C) DDoS attacks

Explanation: Anomaly-based detection using NetFlow is effective at mitigating DDoS attacks by identifying and preventing unauthorized or malicious traffic patterns. DDoS attacks occur when an attacker sends a large number of requests to a network in an attempt to overwhelm the network's resources and disrupt its services. NetFlow data can be analyzed to detect patterns in the traffic and flag any suspicious activity, such as unusually large volumes of traffic or unauthorized traffic. As a result, organizations can take appropriate action to mitigate DDoS attacks, such as implementing firewall rules to block or limit the traffic, and using other security measures to protect against other types of attacks.},
