{"question_id": 4341, "answer": A

Explanation:

When performing vertical or horizontal authentication, the integrity of a request is verified by using a method called message authentication code (MAC). This method concatenates a secret key with a message, then computes a hash or checksum of the concatenated string. The resulting hash or checksum is sent along with the message. The recipient can then recalculate the hash or checksum of the concatenated string using the same secret key. If the two hashes or checksums are equal, the recipient can confirm that the message has not been tampered with.},
