{"question_id": 1440, "answer": 选项C: 包转发},
{"question_id": 1441, "answer": The correct answer is D) Smurf Attack. The Smurf Attack is a type of spoofing attack where an attacker sends a spoofed IP address in the header of a TCP packet to flood the target network with ICMP echo requests (echo). When the target network receives the ICMP echo requests, it responds to the echo requests by sending back ICMP echo replies to the spoofed IP address, causing the target network to enter a half-open state and prevent the completion of the 3-way handshake protocol.},
