FaaS stands for "Function as a Service" (Function-as-a-Service)，which is a cloud computing model where applications are built and run as functions. It differs from other cloud computing models, such as IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service) and PaaS (Platform as a Service), in that it is designed to be more flexible and cost-effective, allowing developers to easily deploy and scale applications without needing to worry about managing the underlying infrastructure.},
